Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with information transmission and outage probabilities, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless relay networks, which are a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes relay selection protocols to improve the performance of the system, which is related to control and optimization of systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the effects of key system parameters on the performance of the system, which is related to multimedia systems. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes and analyzes protocols for energy harvesting in wireless networks, which can be considered as a computational engineering problem.
